\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Son talks with priest:}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\cb4\highlight4 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 You are old enough now to know the truth of it. There are two different approaches to understanding what has been revealed to us in the Four Pillars; you take someone else\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s word for what the scriptures mean, or you can quest the meaning for yourself.\~}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\cb4\highlight4 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 You\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92re saying that what I\u8217\'92ve been taught isn\u8217\'92t true?\~}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\cb4\highlight4 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 No. Certainty in spiritual matters is an illusion. Careful analysis of the Pillars will reveal to you how men like Comtois hide the nuance of the Ogma\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s revelation within practiced sermons and a confident smile. The truth is that the scripture of the Pillars are a guiding light. This light is bright, diffuse, and holy, blinding to us who look into it. One can not outline the sun, lest you go blind. Those of us who claim to see a clear outline of the source are deluded.\~}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\cb4\highlight4 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Speak plainly, good father.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\cb4\highlight4 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 A child\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s mind requires clarity, Domel. The simple story that Comtois taught you as a child filled that need, but you are a man now. You\u8217\'92re going to need to learn to make peace with complexity of reality, for complexity leads to uncertainty, and uncertainty leads to doubt, and from doubt, apostasy.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\cb4\highlight4 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Should I not fulfill what the Emperor commands of me? Is he not Divine?}
\par\pard\plain \li540\fi-270\sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\cb4\highlight4 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Comtois taught you that the Emperor is literally and wholly the Divine Ogma. I say to you that the Emperor is a reflection of it. When you worship the Emperor you worship the Divine vis-a-vis the Emperor.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\cb4\highlight4 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 What is the difference?}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\cb4\highlight4 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 A reflection can be distorted. Look down into the water - you see yourself. In one moment the image is clear, and the water moves, and the next it is fragmented.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\cb4\highlight4 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 As Senka and Dobril looked into the waves Father Comtois interrupts.\~}
